<http://www.spektrix.com/chemainustheatrefestivalsociety/event/28801AVBKQSCSGSCMSTRKBBJTVJRJMRQJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Peril in the Alps";
  schema:description """
	SEP 25 - OCT 25<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>by Steven Dietz<span><br/></span>Based in part on Agatha Christie’s “Poirot Investigates”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Come for a fresh new take on Agatha Christie’s novel transformed into a madcap whodunit thrill ride in the snow-capped Swiss Alps! Can the great Hercule Poirot and his sidekick Captain Hastings must solve a kidnapping case before it gets worse in this frolickingly funny mystery? In the style of the 39 Steps and Baskerville – a sheer delight!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Content Advisory:<span><br/></span>•	Recommended for ages 13+<span><br/></span>•	Mild language<span><br/></span>•	Violence and gunshots<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Join us for lunch or dinner in the Playbill Dining Room!</span> Dining can be added to your order after selecting your theatre tickets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
